>JD: CDMNRRV H1 CR.M +33 240
#note I was cool with this because it sets up VERDANCY and UNVARIED as threats, even though exchanging gives me a better chance of drawing the blank - need to be in scoring range and get lucky with the draw, and exchanging here leaves me down too much.
>Brett_Smitheram: AAAAEEO 2G A.EAE +9 281
#note not sure why this placement. this is actually terrible luck for me that he soaked up all the vowels I needed for UNVARIED/VERDANCY and similar plays, since from my perspective my odds looked pretty good after CREM.
>JD: ?DNORVX A4 NOX +27 267
#note lost the game on this move. I obviously can't play COX because my best chance of winning is to draw UNVARIED, so I need to keep the lane open. I should also play either OX or NOX at A5 to block Q plays like QI and QADI. Unfortunately I was worried about giving up WOX, hence NOX instead of OX, but I must keep the N. Not only that, but I should be deliberately trying to trick him into taking the WOX spot aiming to bingo out! I wanted to play the N to increase my chances of drawing a row 15 bingo, but that looks unlikely anyway. After NOX, I can basically only win if he has an awful Q rack or if I draw into ADENRV? and can bingo out unblockably.
>Brett_Smitheram: AADEIOQ 2C QI +24 305
>JD: ?DINRVW 5I W.N +21 288
